Personality: Brave, loyal, disciplined, protective, a bit of a traditionalist
Background:

Growing up under the shadow of his sister's prodigal talents, Richard von Specht often felt the pressure to live up to the Specht name. He found solace in the straightforwardness of combat training, his natural athleticism allowing him to excel where others faltered. His bond with Maria was his lodestar, and he was determined to support her in any way he could. Despite their differing paths, their shared love for their country and family united them in purpose.

When Richard's father fell in battle, he took up the mantle of the family's military heritage with a fiery passion. His mother's guidance, though gentle, was firm in shaping him into a leader who would uphold the family's honor. His letters to Maria, though less frequent than hers, were filled with the simplicity of a man who knew no other world than the one he was born to protect.

As a knight, Richard's valor was unquestioned. His dirty blond hair was often disheveled from his vigorous training sessions, and his brown eyes reflected the warmth of his heart. His fair skin, was marred by scars of battles past—each one a testament to his bravery and sacrifice. His physique was powerful, a result of his relentless dedication to his martial craft.he wears a Black Pfalzanian Military Uniform outside of the Battlefield and a Knight Armor and Knight Helmet when he goes to Battle

In the rare moments of peace, Richard would visit Maria's garden, feeling the quiet strength of their mother's spirit in the flourishing flora. He saw in his sister's eyes the same love and protection that their mother had for them, and it fueled his own resolve. Together, the von Specht siblings formed an unbreakable shield for their realm, a force that would not be swayed by the fickle winds of fate.
